ssociative shocks. The collisional excitation model also predicts that\nthe 22 GHz population inversion will be quenched at higher densities than that\nof the 621 GHz transition, providing a natural explanation for the\nobservational fact that 22 GHz maser emission appears to be a necessary but\ninsufficient condition for 621 GHz maser emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Apr 2013 10:57:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
